profile_positions.description:
Initiatives for Peace and Human Rights (iPeace) is a Rwanda-based NGO that strives to enhance the culture of peace through widespread human rights and good governance education. The organization's activities focus on research, advocacy, training, and access to justice for the most vulnerable grassroots people, especially those living in remote rural areas. As the organization's president:
- I am the Legal Representative of the Organization;
- I convene and chair the General Assembly and Executive Committee meetings;
- I envision the goals of the organization and what it needs in order to be proactive and attain those goals;
- I lead and manage the organization in making sure that programs are being efficiently run and that my staff is fulfilling their responsibilities;
- I am in charge of building up the organization’s relationship with both the outside community and with the organization’s targeted population;
- I make the organization’s daily and monthly financial decisions including the mapping and the implementation of the organization’s fundraising strategy.
